OL,6,GThe chairman of the BBC has called on
OL,7,Gthe Government to take over funding for
OL,8,Gthe BBC World Service as cuts continue
OL,9,Gto UK-focused services.
OL,11,FSpeaking yesterday, Richard Sharp
OL,12,Fwarned that the BBC would have to make
OL,13,Ffurther cuts to the World Service as
OL,14,Fpart of overall budget reductions.
OL,16,FSharp said the future of the BBC World
OL,17,FService was "in jeopardy" unless the
OL,18,Fgovernment steps in with more money.
OL,3,CUK versus the World (Service): BBC
OL,4,Cchair calls for funding switch
