OL,6,FHe said the BBC was having to ask
OL,7,Fwhether it was right for "audiences in
OL,8,FLeicester, for example, to continue
OL,9,Fpicking up the tab for services in, for
OL,10,Fexample, Lagos".
OL,12,FThere has already been a fierce
OL,13,Fbacklash against cuts to local radio,
OL,14,Findicating further cuts to UK services
OL,15,Fin favour of maintaining international
OL,16,Fservices would face great resistance.
OL,18,FMeanwhile, the National Union of
OL,19,FJournalists' cross-party Parliamentary
OL,20,FGroup is going to meet Ofcom
OL,21,Frepresentatives later this month to
OL,22,Fdiscuss planned and implemented cuts.
