OL,6,FOn the agenda will be the plans for
OL,7,Flocal radio, the closure of local TV in
OL,8,FCambridge and Oxford, the axing of the
OL,9,FBBC Radio Foyle Breakfast Show and the
OL,10,Fclosure of the BBC News Channel and BBC
OL,11,FWorld News, in favour of a combined
OL,12,Fnews channel for audiences around the
OL,13,Fworld and the UK.
OL,15,FThe NUJ says Ofcom will be asked about
OL,16,Fthe impact of these measures on
OL,17,Faudiences and what Ofcom should be
OL,18,Fdoing to protect public service
OL,19,Fbroadcasting and the provision of news
OL,20,Fand current affairs by the BBC.
