OL,6,FThe Government currently pays #94.4
OL,7,Fmillion a year towards the World
OL,8,FService as part of a three-year #283.2m
OL,9,Fagreement, but that amounts to less
OL,10,Fthan a quarter of the World Service's
OL,11,Ftotal annual budget.
OL,13,FEven if Government funding was only
OL,14,Fdoubled to pay for just under half the
OL,15,FWorld Service budget, that would still
OL,16,Fenable the BBC to reduce recent cuts to
OL,17,Flocal radio and TV.
